196
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:45,990
Even a soldier needs a break once in a while.

197
00:16:47,320 --> 00:16:49,220
How strange.



198
00:16:49,220 --> 00:16:51,820
When I'm with you, I feel more relaxed.

199
00:16:53,260 --> 00:16:55,460
Th-Thank you very much.

200
00:17:02,380 --> 00:17:05,860
How about it? Why don't we go out to dinner or something?

201
00:17:06,480 --> 00:17:07,950
Kazamatsuri-san?

202
00:17:14,880 --> 00:17:17,720
Y-Yawara-san, what are you doing here?

203
00:17:18,740 --> 00:17:20,150
It's Inokuma Yawara!

204
00:17:20,150 --> 00:17:21,080
Yawara?

205
00:17:21,080 --> 00:17:22,010
It's really her!

206
00:17:46,710 --> 00:17:48,210
Work?

207
00:17:48,770 --> 00:17:49,710
Yes.

208
00:17:49,710 --> 00:17:52,460
W-Wait a minute! Why that company?

209
00:17:52,460 --> 00:17:53,650
He's right!
W-Wait a minute! Why that company?

210
00:17:53,650 --> 00:17:56,590
You could've done much better for yourself!

211
00:17:56,590 --> 00:17:59,140
That's not the problem here!

212
00:17:59,140 --> 00:18:00,760
What <i>is</i> the problem?

213
00:18:00,760 --> 00:18:04,460
What about your transfer to Saikai U?

214
00:18:04,460 --> 00:18:05,850
So that's it?

215
00:18:06,400 --> 00:18:07,810
I'm not going to Saikai U.

216
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:10,930
What? Then what about judo?

217
00:18:10,930 --> 00:18:13,700
Does Tsurukame Travel even have a team?

218
00:18:13,700 --> 00:18:14,920
No, it doesn't.

219
00:18:14,920 --> 00:18:17,670
